								<a name="content"></a><p class="lead"><strong>From the beginning, the Internet was created to be a very free and open system for the exchange of information. It is that very freedom that has allowed the Internet as well as the Web to grow so quickly and to be a place where almost limitless information can be found and exchanged easily.</strong></p class="lead">
								<hr>
								<p>Since the system itself is so free and open, the Internet and the Web offer users and their computers no protection from malware found on the Web, from damaging programs sent over the Internet or from the people and groups who create them.</p>
								<p>It is up to each user to protect his or her computer. Companies, libraries, schools and other organizations set up these protections for all of the computers within them. At home, individual users must do this for themselves.</p>
								<p>Let's start with learning about malware and other threats found on the Web and the Internet.</p>
							</div>
